<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TVM3.4.3">
<l>paṅkayak kaṇṇa ṉeṉkō pavaḷaccev vāya ṉeṉkō</l>
<l>vaṅkati raṭiya ṉeṉkō vañcaṉa vaṇṇa ṉeṉkō</l>
<l>ceṅkatir muṭiya ṉeṉkō tirumaṟu mārpa ṉeṉkō</l>
<l>caṅkucak karatta ṉeṉkō cātimā ṇikkat taiyē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Will I say “the one with lotus eyes”? Will I say “he with a coral-red mouth”?</l>
<l>Will I say “he with pretty-rayed feet”? Will I say “he with kajal colour”?</l>
<l>Will I say “he with a red-rayed crown” Will I say “he with Śrī as a stain on his chest”</l>
<l>Will I say “he with conch and discus”? – to the ruby by kind.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
